# GOLC safe environment example (CONTEXT D-19).
#
# This file documents every supported environment variable NAME with a
# safe, empty placeholder. It is committed and tracked; the real, populated
# .env stays untracked (see .gitignore). Never fill in a real value here.
#
# Both variables below are optional: they are read only by explicit Linear
# remote commands -- `golc linear preview --remote ...`, `golc linear drift
# --remote --read-only`, and `golc linear apply ...` (Plan 01-15's real
# process transport, internal/command/linear.go). Every offline command --
# bootstrap, check, generate, build, test, and package --foundation --
# never reads this file and never requires either variable to be set.
# .github/workflows/linear-sync.yml is the only place either secret is
# ever materialized in CI: inside a protected/manual workflow_dispatch job,
# written to an ephemeral .env only inside a try/finally that removes it on
# success, failure, and cancellation. Unavailable/unreviewed credentials
# never fail offline acceptance -- real remote synchronization simply stays
# pending until explicitly authorized (CONTEXT D-21).

# Linear API key. Required only to run an explicit Linear remote command.
LINEAR_API_KEY=

# Linear team identifier. Required only to run an explicit Linear remote command.
LINEAR_TEAM_ID=
